name: oq-engine
raw_recipe:
{% set name = "oq-engine" %}
{% set version = "2.9.0" %}
{% set sha256 = "2aae05cb24f68a12d7900aba4bb33fc635643287fcbf2ec9d65e551038ac8629" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://github.com/gem/{{ name }}/archive/v{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 0
  #This recipe currently only runs on Python 3.5,
  #update when oq-engine source supports a different version.
  skip: True  # [not py35]
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools

  #these are all of the dependencies for oq-engine.  Extras are not currently handled,
  #as some of them are not available via conda.
  run:
    - python
    - mock >=1.0,<1.4
    - h5py >=2.2,<2.8
    - nose >=1.3,<1.4
    - numpy >=1.8,<1.12
    - scipy >=0.13,<0.18
    - psutil >=1.2,<4.5
    - shapely >=1.3,<1.6
    - docutils >=0.11,<0.14
    - decorator >=3.4,<4.1
    - django >=1.6,<1.12
    - matplotlib >=1.5,<2.0
    - requests >=2.2,<2.13
    - pyshp >=1.2.3,<1.2.11
    - pyyaml
    
test:
  # Some packages might need a `test/commands` key to check CLI.
  # List all the packages/modules that `run_test.py` imports.
  imports:
    - openquake.hazardlib

about:
  home: https://github.com/gem/oq-engine
  license: GPL-3.0
  license_family: GPL
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'The OpenQuake Engine is an open source application that allows users to compute seismic hazard and seismic risk of earthquakes on a global scale.'

  # The remaining entries in this section are optional, but recommended
  description: |
    The OpenQuake Engine is an open source application that allows users to compute seismic hazard and seismic risk of earthquakes on a global scale. It runs on Linux, macOS and Windows, on laptops, workstations, standalone servers and multi-node clusters.
  doc_url: https://github.com/gem/oq-engine/tree/engine-2.5#openquake-engine
  dev_url: https://github.com/gem/oq-engine

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    # GitHub IDs for maintainers of the recipe.
    # Always check with the people listed below if they are OK becoming maintainers of the recipe. (There will be spam!)
    - mhearne-usgs
